HEADWORD: Norma
<hw>Nor"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A norm; a principle or rule; a model; a standard.</def> <rj><au>J.
S. Mill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A mason's or a carpenter's square or rule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A templet or gauge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Normal</ent>⟦br⟧
